  "texts": [
    "Increasing the number of demonstrations to 8 helps reduce the bias, but RSD remains substantial at around 0.4, and adding further demonstrations results in little to no improvement.",
    "Similarly, we find BiasScore improves considerably when using sufficient demonstrations, with models obtaining values as high as 0.25 when using no demonstrations, to around 0.05 for the best model and setting.",
    "High BiasScore values indicate the model is uncalibrated, and tends to make overly confident predictions on certain labels regardless of the input.",
    "Although BiasScore can be relatively small for some models-indicating their average output distribution is close to uniform-when observed together with high RSD, it implies that the model subtly but persistently assigns more probability mass to the preferred labels, resulting in substantial bias.",
    "We further observe that, interestingly, both bias metrics show divergent trends."
  ],
